# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# packages/api/.dev.vars — LOCAL Worker secrets for `wrangler dev`.
# Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored). For production, set each with:
#   wrangler secret put <NAME>
# Bindings (DB, ENDPOINT_DO) are NOT here — they live in wrangler.toml.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Admin key protecting the /v1/endpoints CRUD routes (you choose to add this
# in phase 1). Any caller managing endpoints must present it. Generate a
# random value, e.g.  openssl rand -hex 32
ADMIN_API_KEY=local-dev-admin-key-change-me

# Master key for envelope-encrypting endpoint credentials (signing_secret,
# ingest_key) at rest in D1. base64 of 32 random bytes, e.g.
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# Required: endpoint create/rotate encrypt with it; delivery + ingestion decrypt
# with it. Rotating THIS key would orphan already-encrypted rows, so treat it as
# long-lived. In production: wrangler secret put SECRET_ENCRYPTION_KEY
SECRET_ENCRYPTION_KEY=base64-of-32-random-bytes-change-me

# NOTE: there is intentionally NO global signing secret here. Each endpoint's
# HMAC signing secret is generated at runtime and stored (encrypted) in D1 (see
# packages/api/src/do/CLAUDE.md). Do not add one.
